title: For Sale/Trade:  Rare Grendel SRT-20F in 7.62X51 NATO
postcontent: Before there was Kel-Tec, there was Grendel. The basis of many of Kel-Tec's current offerings were first produced there under George Kellgren. The SRT-20F was produced in the 80's, and production ceased in the 1990's. They use a Sako A2 action and reciever, Douglas match barrel and specially made muzzle brake. The rifle has a capacity of 9 + 1 and feeds from a fixed internal box magazine. The stock is the most unique feature of the gun, and is capable of folding under the trigger group similar to the Kel-Tec SU-16 series of rifles. The sling swivel is specifically made so the once standard USGI M16 clip-on bipod can be attatched. The gun weighs just 6.7 lbs yet is extremely comfortable to shoot.This particular rifle is outfitted with an older Weaver Tactical 3x9 MilDot scope, sun shade, and nylon sling. This rifle is extremely fun to shoot and has spent most of it's years sitting in a gun safe. I prefer cash, but any interesting and fair trades will be acceptable as well.
